==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trapan
<hw>Tra*pan"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>trappan</ets>. See <er>Trap</er>, and cf. <er>Trepan</er> a
snare.]</ety> <def>A snare; a stratagem; a trepan. See 3d
<er>Trepan</er>.</def> <rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trapan</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Trapan
<hw>Tra*pan"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Trapanned</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Trapanning</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To insnare; to catch by
stratagem; to entrap; to trepan.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Having some of his people <qex>trapanned</qex> at Baldivia.</q>
<rj><qau>Anson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

